ref_solution:
$\underline{\text{Method 1}}$

Make a diagram and draw $4$ lines so that they intersect each other as shown. The number of different sections is $\boxed{11}.$

[asy]

draw((0,0)--(6,0)--(6,4)--(0,4)--(0,0));

draw((2,0)--(4,4));

label("N",(4,4),N);
label("M",(2,0),S);

