Also, let $\omega^2 = \overline{\omega}$, so $\overline{\omega} = \omega^2$.

First, note that
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{a_1 + \omega} + \frac{1}{a_2 + \omega} + \dots + \frac{1}{a_n + \omega} &= 2 + 5i\\
\Rightarrow\qquad\frac{1}{a_1 + \omega^2} + \frac{1}{a_2 + \omega^2} + \dots + \frac{1}{a_n + \omega^2} &= 2 - 5i\\
\Rightarrow\qquad\frac{1}{\overline{a_1} + \omega} + \frac{1}{\overline{a_2} + \omega} + \dots + \frac{1}{\overline{a_n} + \omega} &= 2 - 5i.
\end{align*}
Summing these two equations, we obtain
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{a_1 + \omega} + \frac{1}{a_2 + \omega} + \dots + \frac{1}{a_n + \omega} + \frac{1}{\overline{a_1} + \omega} + \frac{1}{\overline{a_2} + \omega} + \dots + \frac{1}{\overline{a_n} + \omega} &= 4.
\end{align*}
Noting that $\overline{\frac{1}{a_i + \omega}} = \frac{1}{\overline{a_i} + \omega}$ for each $i$, we can rewrite the above as
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{a_1 + \omega} + \frac{1}{\overline{a_1} + \omega} + \frac{1}{a_2 + \omega} + \frac{1}{\overline{a_2} + \omega} + \dots + \frac{1}{a_n + \omega} + \frac{1}{\overline{a_n} + \omega} &= 4\\
\Rightarrow\qquad\sum_{i=1}^n \left(\frac{1}{a_i + \omega} + \frac{1}{\overline{a_i} + \omega}\right) &= 4.
\end{align*}
Since $\omega^2 + \omega + 1 = 0$, we have
\begin{align*}
\sum_{i=1}^n \left(\frac{1}{a_i + \omega} + \frac{1}{\overline{a_i} + \omega}\right) &= \sum_{i=1}^n \left(\frac{(a_i + \omega) + (\overline{a_i} + \omega)}{(a_i + \omega)(\overline{a_i} + \omega)}\right)\\
&= \sum_{i=1}^n \left(\frac{a_i + \overline{a_i} + 2}{a_i^2 + a_i + 1}\right)\\
&= \sum_{i=1}^n \left(\frac{2a_i - 1}{a_i^2 - a_i + 1}\right).
\end{align*}
Thus, we have $\boxed{\sum_{i=1}^n \left(\frac{2a_i - 1}{a_i^2 - a_i + 1}\right) = 4}$.
